        "section_value": "The patient's presentation is most concerning for unstable angina, given her history of diabetes, high blood pressure, and reported chest pain. Further investigation is warranted to rule out coronary artery disease.\nPlan\nI am going to order aspirin daily, a baby aspirin, and nitroglycerin for use if chest pain persists. I will also order a hemoglobin a1c test and schedule a follow-up appointment in two weeks. I am going to start hydrochlorothiazide to help with blood pressure and edema. I will also recommend monitoring devices and encourage you to enter your blood pressure readings into Epic MyChart. I will refer you to cardiology for a stress test to evaluate your heart function. Please call 911 if you experience chest pain and do not improve with nitroglycerin.",
